<p>If I use <code>@html.Raw()</code> Html is executing very well.. but some people saying that displaying data(html) using <code>@html.Raw()</code> will lead to XSS attacks.</p>  <p>But alternatively we don't have any choice to display html data in mvc... Is there any way to achieve this?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;h1 class="art-heading"&gt;@Html.DisplayFor(model =&gt; model.Article_Name)&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;div&gt;     @Html.DisplayFor(model =&gt; model.Article_Content) &lt;/div&gt; &lt;section&gt;     @Html.Raw(Model.code) &lt;/section&gt; </code></pre>